FLUTTER PACKAGE RESEARCH FOR UNJYNX EXPANSION
===============================================
Last updated: 2026-03-09
Source: Context7 MCP + pub.dev docs

1. HOME SCREEN WIDGETS (W1-W5)
   Package: home_widget ^6.0.0

   Flutter side:
     HomeWidget.saveWidgetData<String>('id', data)    -- save data for native widget
     HomeWidget.updateWidget(
       name: 'UnjynxTasksWidgetProvider',
       androidName: 'UnjynxTasksWidgetProvider',
       iOSName: 'UnjynxTasksWidget',
     )    -- trigger native widget update
     HomeWidget.registerInteractivityCallback(backgroundCallback)  -- handle taps from widget

   iOS (SwiftUI):
     - Uses WidgetKit + AppIntent bridge
     - AppIntent calls HomeWidgetBackgroundWorker.run(url:, appGroup:)
     - Reads data from UserDefaults (shared via App Group)

   Android (Jetpack Compose or XML):
     - AppWidgetProvider with RemoteViews
     - Reads from SharedPreferences via HomeWidgetPlugin.getData(context)
     - Can display images rendered by Flutter (BitmapFactory.decodeFile)

   Update frequency: 15 min via WidgetKit timeline + on-demand via HomeWidget.updateWidget()

2. CALENDAR (F1-F2)
   Package: calendar_view (flutter_calendar_view) ^2.2.0
   Library ID: /simformsolutionspvtltd/flutter_calendar_view
   Benchmark: 85.7/100 (BEST option)

   Key widgets:
     MonthView<Object?>()  -- month calendar grid
     DayView<Object?>()    -- 24h timeline with event tiles
     WeekView<Object?>()   -- 7-column grid

   Features:
     - EventController() for managing events
     - RecurrenceSettings(frequency: RepeatFrequency.weekly, weekdays: [0,2,4])
     - Custom eventTileBuilder for branded task blocks
     - heightPerMinute: 1.0 for day view scaling
     - startHour/endHour to limit visible hours
     - liveTimeIndicatorSettings for current time line
     - onEventTap, onDateLongPress callbacks
     - fullDayEventBuilder for all-day events
     - Drag to reschedule (via custom gesture handlers)

   For UNJYNX:
     - F1: Use MonthView (month), WeekView (week/3-day), DayView (day)
     - Segmented control to switch views
     - Custom cell builder for task count dots (month view)
     - Custom event tile builder with project color coding
     - Color intensity heatmap in month view (via custom cell builder)

   Alternative: table_calendar ^3.1.0 (also good but less feature-rich)

3. CHARTS (I2 Progress Dashboard)
   Package: fl_chart ^0.70.0
   Library ID: /websites/pub_dev_fl_chart (1506 snippets, High reputation)

   Chart types needed for I2:
     - LineChart: completion trend (daily/weekly/monthly)
     - BarChart: productivity by day, focus time
     - ScatterChart: estimated vs actual time
     - PieChart (donut): category breakdown

   All charts use UNJYNX brand colors (purple/gold/emerald)

4. HEATMAP (I1 Progress Hub)
   Package: flutter_heatmap_calendar ^1.0.0 OR custom CustomPainter
   Library ID: /devappmin/flutter_heatmap_calendar

   For UNJYNX:
     - GitHub-style 52-week contribution grid
     - Custom painter preferred for full brand control
     - Color scale: empty(dark) → light purple → deep violet → gold
     - Tap any day → popup with task count
     - Free: 30 days, Pro: full year

5. NLP TASK PARSING (v1 - rule-based)
   Backend package: chrono-node ^2.7.0 (natural language date parser)
   Frontend: Custom Dart regex parser + intl package

   Pattern matching:
     - Date: "Monday", "tomorrow", "March 15", "next week"
     - Time: "9am", "at 3:30", "morning", "evening"
     - Priority: "urgent", "!", "P1", "high priority"
     - Project: "#ProjectName", "in Shopping"

   Flow: User types → Dart regex extracts → shows parsed preview → on submit,
         backend validates with chrono-node if needed

6. ADDITIONAL PACKAGES REFERENCED
   - lottie ^3.0.0: Lottie animations for empty states, streak flame
   - flutter_slidable ^3.1.0: Swipe actions on task cards
   - flutter_quill ^10.0.0: Rich text editing for task descriptions (D2)
   - rrule ^0.3.0: RRULE parsing/generation for D5 recurring builder
   - file_picker ^8.0.0: Task import CSV selection
   - csv ^6.0.0: CSV parsing for task import
   - share_plus ^9.0.0: Share daily content as cards
   - purchases_flutter ^8.0.0: RevenueCat billing SDK
   - google_fonts ^6.2.0: Outfit, DM Sans, Bebas Neue, Playfair Display
   - flutter_svg ^2.0.0: Custom brand SVG icons
   - audioplayers ^6.0.0: Sound effects (task complete, streaks)
   - vibration ^2.0.0: Custom haptic patterns
   - flutter_tts ^4.0.0: Voice-first accessibility mode
   - OpenDyslexic font: Via google_fonts or bundled asset for dyslexia mode
